  "title": "Staff Nurse_GP Clinic",
  "description": "<p><u><strong>Job Description</strong></u></p><ul><li>Perform front-desk duties including patient registration, appointment booking, dispensing of medication, billing, and payment collection.</li><li>Attend to patient enquiries and provide a positive patient care experience.</li><li>Support doctors in clinical procedures, including chaperoning, vaccinations, blood taking, wound dressing, monitoring vital signs, and coordination of laboratory/diagnostic services.</li><li>Provide nursing care, including history taking, patient education, counselling, and dispensing.</li><li>Carry out administrative tasks such as claims submission, stock management, and clinic audits.</li><li>Perform other duties related to patient care and clinic operations as assigned.</li></ul><p><u><strong>Job Requirements</strong></u></p><ul><li>5.5-day rotating shift (AM, Noon & Evening) workweek (Weekday + 1 Weekend (Either Saturday or Sunday).</li><li>No overnight shifts.</li><li>Minimum qualification: Diploma in Nursing</li><li>Possess a valid practicing certificate (Singapore Nursing Board)</li><li>Good communication and interpersonal skills</li><li>BCLS & AED Certified</li></ul><p><u><strong>Advantage (Not Mandatory)</strong></u></p><ul><li>Familiarity with Plato CMS.</li><li>Experience in submission of insurance and Medisave claims.</li><li>Proficiency in Mandarin/Dialects is an advantage to assist non-English-speaking elderly patients. (This is included as a job necessity rather than a preference to align with fair hiring practices.)</li></ul>",
